  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Call to Return to the '
      title: 'A Call to Return to the '
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  In the eighth month, in the second year
        of Darius, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to the prophet
        Zechariah, the son of Berechiah, son of Iddo, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was very angry with your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore say to them, Thus declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts: Return to me, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, and
        I will return to you, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Do not be like your fathers, to whom the former prophets cried out,
        \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, Return from your
        evil ways and from your evil deeds.\u2019 But they did not hear or pay attention
        to me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Your fathers, where are they? And the prophets, do they live forever? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: A Vision of a Horseman'
      title: A Vision of a Horseman
      number: 6
      content: "But my words and my statutes, which I commanded my servants the prophets,
        did they not overtake your fathers? So they repented and said, \u2018As the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts purposed to deal with us for our ways
        and deeds, so has he dealt with us.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'On the twenty-fourth day of the eleventh month, which is the month
        of Shebat, in the second year of Darius, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to the prophet Zechariah, the son of Berechiah, son of Iddo, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CI saw in the night, and behold, a man riding on a red horse!
        He was standing among the myrtle trees in the glen, and behind him were red,
        sorrel, and white horses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then I said, \u2018What are these, my lord?\u2019 The angel who talked
        with me said to me, \u2018I will show you what they are.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the man who was standing among the myrtle trees answered, \u2018These
        are they whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent to patrol the earth.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And they answered the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who
        was standing among the myrtle trees, and said, \u2018We have patrolled the
        earth, and behold, all the earth remains at rest.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u2018O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, how long will you have no mercy on Jerusalem and the cities of
        Judah, against which you have been angry these seventy years?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answered gracious and comforting
        words to the angel who talked with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the angel who talked with me said to me, \u2018Cry out, Thus says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: I am exceedingly jealous for Jerusalem
        and for Zion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And I am exceedingly angry with the nations that are at ease; for
        while I was angry but a little, they furthered the disaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore, thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I have returned
        to Jerusalem with mercy; my house shall be built in it, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, and the measuring line shall be stretched out over Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: A Vision of Horns and Craftsmen'
      title: A Vision of Horns and Craftsmen
      number: 17
      content: "Cry out again, Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts:
        My cities shall again overflow with prosperity, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will again comfort Zion and again choose Jerusalem.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]] And I lifted my eyes and saw, and behold, four horns! '
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        content: '  Ch 2:1 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And I said to the angel who talked with me, \u201CWhat are these?\u201D
        And he said to me, \u201CThese are the horns that have scattered Judah, Israel,
        and Jerusalem.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> showed me four craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And I said, \u201CWhat are these coming to do?\u201D He said, \u201CThese
        are the horns that scattered Judah, so that no one raised his head. And these
        have come to terrify them, to cast down the horns of the nations who lifted
        up their horns against the land of Judah to scatter it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Vision of a Man with a Measuring Line'
      title: A Vision of a Man with a Measuring Line
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]] And I lifted my eyes and saw, and behold, a man
        with a measuring line in his hand! '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: '  Ch 2:5 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then I said, \u201CWhere are you going?\u201D And he said to me,
        \u201CTo measure Jerusalem, to see what is its width and what is its length.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And behold, the angel who talked with me came forward, and another
        angel came forward to meet him '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and said to him, \u201CRun, say to that young man, \u2018Jerusalem
        shall be inhabited as villages without walls, because of the multitude of
        people and livestock in it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I will be to her a wall of fire all around, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and I will be the glory in her midst.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Up! Up! Flee from the land of the north, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        For I have spread you abroad as the four winds of the heavens, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Up! Escape to Zion, you who dwell with the daughter of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For thus said the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, after his
        glory sent me[[COMMENT(0)]] to the nations who plundered you, for he who
        touches you touches the apple of his eye: '
      comments:
      - number: '2:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBehold, I will shake my hand over them, and they shall become
        plunder for those who served them. Then you will know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts has sent me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Sing and rejoice, O daughter of Zion, for behold, I come and I will
        dwell in your midst, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And many nations shall join themselves to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in that day, and shall be my people. And I will dwell in your midst, and
        you shall know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has sent me
        to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will inherit Judah as his portion
        in the holy land, and will again choose Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Be silent, all flesh, before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for
        he has roused himself from his holy dwelling.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Vision of Joshua the High Priest'
      title: A Vision of Joshua the High Priest
      number: 1
      content: '  Then he showed me Joshua the high priest standing before the angel
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and Satan[[COMMENT(0)]] standing at his
        right hand to accuse him. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Satan, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        rebuke you, O Satan! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who has chosen Jerusalem
        rebuke you! Is not this a brand[[COMMENT(0)]] plucked from the fire?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: That is, a burning stick
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Joshua was standing before the angel, clothed with filthy garments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the angel said to those who were standing before him, \u201CRemove
        the filthy garments from him.\u201D And to him he said, \u201CBehold, I have
        taken your iniquity away from you, and I will clothe you with pure vestments.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I said, \u201CLet them put a clean turban on his head.\u201D
        So they put a clean turban on his head and clothed him with garments. And
        the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was standing by.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> solemnly assured
        Joshua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: If you
        will walk in my ways and keep my charge, then you shall rule my house and
        have charge of my courts, and I will give you the right of access among those
        who are standing here. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Hear now, O Joshua the high priest, you and your friends who sit
        before you, for they are men who are a sign: behold, I will bring my servant
        the Branch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For behold, on the stone that I have set before Joshua, on a single
        stone with seven eyes,[[COMMENT(0)]] I will engrave its inscription, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, and I will remove the iniquity
        of this land in a single day. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "In that day, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, every
        one of you will invite his neighbor to come under his vine and under his
        fig tree.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Vision of a Golden Lampstand'
      title: A Vision of a Golden Lampstand
      number: 1
      content: '  And the angel who talked with me came again and woke me, like a
        man who is awakened out of his sleep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CWhat do you see?\u201D I said, \u201CI see,
        and behold, a lampstand all of gold, with a bowl on the top of it, and seven
        lamps on it, with seven lips on each of the lamps that are on the top of
        it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And there are two olive trees by it, one on the right of the bowl
        and the other on its left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I said to the angel who talked with me, \u201CWhat are these,
        my lord?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the angel who talked with me answered and said to me, \u201CDo
        you not know what these are?\u201D I said, \u201CNo, my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CThis is the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to Zerubbabel: Not by might, nor by power, but by my Spirit, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Who are you, O great mountain? Before Zerubbabel you shall become
        a plain. And he shall bring forward the top stone amid shouts of \u2018Grace,
        grace to it!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThe hands of Zerubbabel have laid the foundation of this house;
        his hands shall also complete it. Then you will know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts has sent me to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For whoever has despised the day of small things shall rejoice, and
        shall see the plumb line in the hand of Zerubbabel.  \u201CThese seven are
        the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which range through the whole
        earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I said to him, \u201CWhat are these two olive trees on the right
        and the left of the lampstand?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And a second time I answered and said to him, \u201CWhat are these
        two branches of the olive trees, which are beside the two golden pipes from
        which the golden oil[[COMMENT(0)]] is poured out?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '4:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He said to me, \u201CDo you not know what these are?\u201D I said,
        \u201CNo, my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said, \u201CThese are the two anointed ones[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who stand by the Lord of the whole earth.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '4:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Vision of a Flying Scroll'
      title: A Vision of a Flying Scroll
      number: 1
      content: '  Again I lifted my eyes and saw, and behold, a flying scroll! '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CWhat do you see?\u201D I answered, \u201CI
        see a flying scroll. Its length is twenty cubits, and its width ten cubits.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CThis is the curse that goes out over the
        face of the whole land. For everyone who steals shall be cleaned out according
        to what is on one side, and everyone who swears falsely[[COMMENT(0)]] shall
        be cleaned out according to what is on the other side. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:3 '
        content: Hebrew lacks (supplied from verse 4)
    - name: '4: A Vision of a Woman in a Basket'
      title: A Vision of a Woman in a Basket
      number: 4
      content: "I will send it out, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts,
        and it shall enter the house of the thief, and the house of him who swears
        falsely by my name. And it shall remain in his house and consume it, both
        timber and stones.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  Then the angel who talked with me came forward and said to me,
        \u201CLift your eyes and see what this is that is going out.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And I said, \u201CWhat is it?\u201D He said, \u201CThis is the basket[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that is going out.\u201D And he said, \u201CThis is their iniquity in all
        the land.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        content: "Hebrew ; also verses 7\u201311. An was about 3/5 bushel or 22 litersOne
          Hebrew manuscript, Septuagint, Syriac; most Hebrew manuscripts "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And behold, the leaden cover was lifted, and there was a woman sitting
        in the basket! '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said, \u201CThis is Wickedness.\u201D And he thrust her back
        into the basket, and thrust down the leaden weight on its opening.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then I lifted my eyes and saw, and behold, two women coming forward!
        The wind was in their wings. They had wings like the wings of a stork, and
        they lifted up the basket between earth and heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then I said to the angel who talked with me, \u201CWhere are they
        taking the basket?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said to me, \u201CTo the land of Shinar, to build a house for
        it. And when this is prepared, they will set the basket down there on its
        base.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Vision of Four Chariots'
      title: A Vision of Four Chariots
      number: 1
      content: '  Again I lifted my eyes and saw, and behold, four chariots came
        out from between two mountains. And the mountains were mountains of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The first chariot had red horses, the second black horses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "the third white horses, and the fourth chariot dappled horses\u2014all
        of them strong.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I answered and said to the angel who talked with me, \u201CWhat
        are these, my lord?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the angel answered and said to me, \u201CThese are going out
        to the four winds of heaven, after presenting themselves before the Lord
        of all the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The chariot with the black horses goes toward the north country,
        the white ones go after them, and the dappled ones go toward the south country.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the strong horses came out, they were impatient to go and patrol
        the earth. And he said, \u201CGo, patrol the earth.\u201D So they patrolled
        the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Crown and the Temple'
      title: The Crown and the Temple
      number: 8
      content: "Then he cried to me, \u201CBehold, those who go toward the north
        country have set my Spirit at rest in the north country.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTake from the exiles Heldai, Tobijah, and Jedaiah, who have
        arrived from Babylon, and go the same day to the house of Josiah, the son
        of Zephaniah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Take from them silver and gold, and make a crown, and set it on the
        head of Joshua, the son of Jehozadak, the high priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And say to him, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        hosts, \u201CBehold, the man whose name is the Branch: for he shall branch
        out from his place, and he shall build the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "It is he who shall build the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        and shall bear royal honor, and shall sit and rule on his throne. And there[[COMMENT(0)]]
        shall be a priest on his throne, and the counsel of peace shall be between
        them both.\u201D\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '6:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the crown shall be in the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as a reminder to Helem,[[COMMENT(0)]]  Tobijah, Jedaiah, and Hen the son
        of Zephaniah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:14 '
        content: An alternate spelling of (verse 10)
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  \u201CAnd those who are far off shall come and help to build the
        temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And you shall know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts has sent me to you. And this shall come to pass, if you will diligently
        obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Call for Justice and Mercy'
      title: A Call for Justice and Mercy
      number: 1
      content: '    In the fourth year of King Darius, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to Zechariah on the fourth day of the ninth month, which is Chislev. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the people of Bethel had sent Sharezer and Regem-melech and their
        men to entreat the favor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "saying to the priests of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts and the prophets, \u201CShould I weep and abstain in the fifth month,
        as I have done for so many years?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts came to
        me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CSay to all the people of the land and the priests, \u2018When
        you fasted and mourned in the fifth month and in the seventh, for these seventy
        years, was it for me that you fasted? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when you eat and when you drink, do you not eat for yourselves
        and drink for yourselves? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Were not these the words that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> proclaimed
        by the former prophets, when Jerusalem was inhabited and prosperous, with
        her cities around her, and the South and the lowland were inhabited?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Zechariah,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, Render
        true judgments, show kindness and mercy to one another, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "do not oppress the widow, the fatherless, the sojourner, or the poor,
        and let none of you devise evil against another in your heart.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But they refused to pay attention and turned a stubborn shoulder
        and stopped their ears that they might not hear.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:11 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They made their hearts diamond-hard lest they should hear the law
        and the words that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts had sent by his
        Spirit through the former prophets. Therefore great anger came from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CAs I[[COMMENT(0)]] called, and they would not hear, so they
        called, and I would not hear,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, "
      comments:
      - number: '7:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201Cand I scattered them with a whirlwind among all the nations
        that they had not known. Thus the land they left was desolate, so that no
        one went to and fro, and the pleasant land was made desolate.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Coming Peace and Prosperity of Zion'
      title: The Coming Peace and Prosperity of Zion
      number: 1
      content: '  And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts came,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: I am jealous
        for Zion with great jealousy, and I am jealous for her with great wrath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: I have returned to Zion
        and will dwell in the midst of Jerusalem, and Jerusalem shall be called the
        faithful city, and the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts,
        the holy mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: Old men and old
        women shall again sit in the streets of Jerusalem, each with staff in hand
        because of great age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the streets of the city shall be full of boys and girls playing
        in its streets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: If it is marvelous
        in the sight of the remnant of this people in those days, should it also
        be marvelous in my sight, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: Behold, I will
        save my people from the east country and from the west country, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and I will bring them to dwell in the midst of Jerusalem. And they
        shall be my people, and I will be their God, in faithfulness and in righteousness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: \u201CLet your
        hands be strong, you who in these days have been hearing these words from
        the mouth of the prophets who were present on the day that the foundation
        of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts was laid, that the
        temple might be built. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For before those days there was no wage for man or any wage for beast,
        neither was there any safety from the foe for him who went out or came in,
        for I set every man against his neighbor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But now I will not deal with the remnant of this people as in the
        former days, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For there shall be a sowing of peace. The vine shall give its fruit,
        and the ground shall give its produce, and the heavens shall give their dew.
        And I will cause the remnant of this people to possess all these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And as you have been a byword of cursing among the nations, O house
        of Judah and house of Israel, so will I save you, and you shall be a blessing.
        Fear not, but let your hands be strong.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: \u201CAs
        I purposed to bring disaster to you when your fathers provoked me to wrath,
        and I did not relent, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'so again have I purposed in these days to bring good to Jerusalem
        and to the house of Judah; fear not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These are the things that you shall do: Speak the truth to one another;
        render in your gates judgments that are true and make for peace; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "do not devise evil in your hearts against one another, and love no
        false oath, for all these things I hate, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts came to
        me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: The fast
        of the fourth month and the fast of the fifth and the fast of the seventh
        and the fast of the tenth shall be to the house of Judah seasons of joy and
        gladness and cheerful feasts. Therefore love truth and peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: Peoples
        shall yet come, even the inhabitants of many cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The inhabitants of one city shall go to another, saying, \u2018Let
        us go at once to entreat the favor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        to seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts; I myself am going.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Many peoples and strong nations shall come to seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts in Jerusalem and to entreat the favor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: In those days
        ten men from the nations of every tongue shall take hold of the robe of a
        Jew, saying, \u2018Let us go with you, for we have heard that God is with
        you.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judgment on Israel\u2019s Enemies"
      title: "Judgment on Israel\u2019s Enemies"
      number: 1
      content: '  The oracle of the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is against
        the land of Hadrachand Damascus is its resting place.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has an eye on mankindand on all the tribes of Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        content: 'Or <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  and on Hamath also, which borders on it,  Tyre and Sidon, though
        they are very wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Tyre has built herself a rampartand heaped up silver like dust,and
        fine gold like the mud of the streets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But behold, the Lord will strip her of her possessionsand strike
        down her power on the sea,and she shall be devoured by fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Ashkelon shall see it, and be afraid;Gaza too, and shall writhe
        in anguish;Ekron also, because its hopes are confounded.The king shall perish
        from Gaza;Ashkelon shall be uninhabited;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  a mixed people[[COMMENT(0)]] shall dwell in Ashdod,and I will cut
        off the pride of Philistia.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:6 '
        content: 'Or ; Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will take away its blood from its mouth,and its abominations from
        between its teeth;  it too shall be a remnant for our God;it shall be like
        a clan in Judah,and Ekron shall be like the Jebusites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Coming King of Zion'
      title: The Coming King of Zion
      number: 8
      content: 'Then I will encamp at my house as a guard,  so that none shall march
        to and fro;  no oppressor shall again march over them,  for now I see with
        my own eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Rejoice greatly, O daughter of Zion!Shout aloud, O daughter of
        Jerusalem!  Behold, your king is coming to you;righteous and having salvation
        is he,  humble and mounted on a donkey,on a colt, the foal of a donkey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  I will cut off the chariot from Ephraimand the war horse from Jerusalem;and
        the battle bow shall be cut off,and he shall speak peace to the nations; 
        his rule shall be from sea to sea,and from the River[[COMMENT(0)]] to the
        ends of the earth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:10 '
        content: That is, the Euphrates
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As for you also, because of the blood of my covenant with you,  I
        will set your prisoners free from the waterless pit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Return to your stronghold, O prisoners of hope;today I declare that
        I will restore to you double.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The  Will Save His People'
      title: The  Will Save His People
      number: 13
      content: "For I have bent Judah as my bow;I have made Ephraim its arrow.I will
        stir up your sons, O Zion,against your sons, O Greece,and wield you like
        a warrior\u2019s sword.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will appear over them,and his
        arrow will go forth like lightning;  the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        will sound the trumpetand will march forth in the whirlwinds of the south.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts will protect them,and they
        shall devour, and tread down the sling stones,and they shall drink and roar
        as if drunk with wine,and be full like a bowl,drenched like the corners of
        the altar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'On that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God will save them,as
        the flock of his people;for like the jewels of a crownthey shall shine on
        his land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  For how great is his goodness, and how great his beauty!  Grain
        shall make the young men flourish,and new wine the young women.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Restoration for Judah and Israel'
      title: The Restoration for Judah and Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  Ask rain from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>in the season of the
        spring rain,from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  who makes the storm clouds,and
        he will give them showers of rain,to everyone the vegetation in the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the household gods utter nonsense,and the diviners see lies; 
        they tell false dreamsand give empty consolation.Therefore the people wander
        like sheep;they are afflicted for lack of a shepherd.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u201CMy anger is hot against the shepherds,and I will punish the
        leaders;[[COMMENT(0)]]for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts cares
        for his flock, the house of Judah,and will make them like his majestic steed
        in battle.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "From him shall come the cornerstone,from him the tent peg,from him
        the battle bow,from him every ruler\u2014all of them together.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They shall be like mighty men in battle,  trampling the foe in the
        mud of the streets;they shall fight because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is with them,and they shall put to shame the riders on horses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201CI will strengthen the house of Judah,and I will save the
        house of Joseph.  I will bring them back because I have compassion on them,and
        they shall be as though I had not rejected them,for I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God and I will answer them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Ephraim shall become like a mighty warrior,and their hearts
        shall be glad as with wine.Their children shall see it and be glad;their
        hearts shall rejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  \u201CI will whistle for them and gather them in,for I have redeemed
        them,and they shall be as many as they were before.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Though I scattered them among the nations,yet in far countries
        they shall remember me,and with their children they shall live and return.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  I will bring them home from the land of Egypt,and gather them from
        Assyria,and I will bring them to the land of Gilead and to Lebanon,  till
        there is no room for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  He shall pass through the sea of troublesand strike down the waves
        of the sea,  and all the depths of the Nile shall be dried up.The pride of
        Assyria shall be laid low,and the scepter of Egypt shall depart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  I will make them strong in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        they shall walk in his name,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Flock Doomed to Slaughter'
      title: The Flock Doomed to Slaughter
      number: 1
      content: '  Open your doors, O Lebanon,that the fire may devour your cedars!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Wail, O cypress, for the cedar has fallen,for the glorious trees
        are ruined!Wail, oaks of Bashan,for the thick forest has been felled!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sound of the wail of the shepherds,for their glory is ruined!The
        sound of the roar of the lions,  for the thicket of the Jordan is ruined!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus said the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God: \u201CBecome shepherd
        of the flock doomed to slaughter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Those who buy them slaughter them and go unpunished, and those who
        sell them say, \u2018Blessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I have become
        rich,\u2019 and their own shepherds have no pity on them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For I will no longer have pity on the inhabitants of this land, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Behold, I will cause each of them to fall
        into the hand of his neighbor, and each into the hand of his king, and they
        shall crush the land, and I will deliver none from their hand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  So I became the shepherd of the flock doomed to be slaughtered
        by the sheep traders. And I took two staffs, one I named Favor, the other
        I named Union. And I tended the sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In one month I destroyed the three shepherds. But I became impatient
        with them, and they also detested me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So I said, \u201CI will not be your shepherd. What is to die, let
        it die. What is to be destroyed, let it be destroyed. And let those who are
        left devour the flesh of one another.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I took my staff Favor, and I broke it, annulling the covenant
        that I had made with all the peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So it was annulled on that day, and the sheep traders, who were watching
        me, knew that it was the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then I said to them, \u201CIf it seems good to you, give me my wages;
        but if not, keep them.\u201D And they weighed out as my wages thirty pieces
        of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CThrow it to
        the potter\u201D\u2014the lordly price at which I was priced by them. So
        I took the thirty pieces of silver and threw them into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        to the potter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then I broke my second staff Union, annulling the brotherhood between
        Judah and Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CTake once
        more the equipment of a foolish shepherd. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For behold, I am raising up in the land a shepherd who does not care
        for those being destroyed, or seek the young or heal the maimed or nourish
        the healthy, but devours the flesh of the fat ones, tearing off even their
        hoofs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201CWoe to my worthless shepherd,  who deserts the flock!May
        the sword strike his armand his right eye!Let his arm be wholly withered,his
        right eye utterly blinded!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Will Give Salvation'
      title: The  Will Give Salvation
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    The oracle of the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        concerning Israel: Thus declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who stretched
        out the heavens and founded the earth and formed the spirit of man within
        him: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am about to make Jerusalem a cup of staggering to
        all the surrounding peoples. The siege of Jerusalem will also be against
        Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'On that day I will make Jerusalem a heavy stone for all the peoples.
        All who lift it will surely hurt themselves. And all the nations of the earth
        will gather against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On that day, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I will strike
        every horse with panic, and its rider with madness. But for the sake of the
        house of Judah I will keep my eyes open, when I strike every horse of the
        peoples with blindness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the clans of Judah shall say to themselves, \u2018The inhabitants
        of Jerusalem have strength through the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts,
        their God.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201COn that day I will make the clans of Judah like a blazing
        pot in the midst of wood, like a flaming torch among sheaves. And they shall
        devour to the right and to the left all the surrounding peoples, while Jerusalem
        shall again be inhabited in its place, in Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAnd the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give salvation to
        the tents of Judah first, that the glory of the house of David and the glory
        of the inhabitants of Jerusalem may not surpass that of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'On that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will protect the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem, so that the feeblest among them on that day shall be like David,
        and the house of David shall be like God, like the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        going before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Him Whom They Have Pierced'
      title: Him Whom They Have Pierced
      number: 9
      content: 'And on that day I will seek to destroy all the nations that come
        against Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd I will pour out on the house of David and the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem a spirit of grace and pleas for mercy, so that, when they look
        on me, on him whom they have pierced, they shall mourn for him, as one mourns
        for an only child, and weep bitterly over him, as one weeps over a firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'On that day the mourning in Jerusalem will be as great as the mourning
        for Hadad-rimmon in the plain of Megiddo. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The land shall mourn, each family[[COMMENT(0)]] by itself: the family
        of the house of David by itself, and their wives by themselves; the family
        of the house of Nathan by itself, and their wives by themselves; '
      comments:
      - number: '12:12 '
        content: "Or ; throughout verses 12\u201314"
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the family of the house of Levi by itself, and their wives by themselves;
        the family of the Shimeites by itself, and their wives by themselves; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: and all the families that are left, each by itself, and their wives
        by themselves.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Idolatry Cut Off'
      title: Idolatry Cut Off
      number: 1
      content: "    \u201COn that day there shall be a fountain opened for the house
        of David and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, to cleanse them from sin and uncleanness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CAnd on that day, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        hosts, I will cut off the names of the idols from the land, so that they
        shall be remembered no more. And also I will remove from the land the prophets
        and the spirit of uncleanness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And if anyone again prophesies, his father and mother who bore him
        will say to him, \u2018You shall not live, for you speak lies in the name
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019 And his father and mother who bore
        him shall pierce him through when he prophesies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201COn that day every prophet will be ashamed of his vision when
        he prophesies. He will not put on a hairy cloak in order to deceive, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "but he will say, \u2018I am no prophet, I am a worker of the soil,
        for a man sold me in my youth.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: The Shepherd Struck'
      title: The Shepherd Struck
      number: 6
      content: "And if one asks him, \u2018What are these wounds on your back?\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]
        he will say, \u2018The wounds I received in the house of my friends.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        content: 'Or ; Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAwake, O sword, against my shepherd,against the man who stands
        next to me,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.  \u201CStrike
        the shepherd, and the sheep will be scattered;I will turn my hand against
        the little ones.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the whole land, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,two thirds
        shall be cut off and perish,  and one third shall be left alive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And I will put this third into the fire,and refine them as one refines
        silver,and test them as gold is tested.  They will call upon my name,and
        I will answer them.  I will say, \u2018They are my people\u2019;and they
        will say, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is my God.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Coming Day of the '
      title: 'The Coming Day of the '
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Behold, a day is coming for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when the spoil taken from you will be divided in your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For I will gather all the nations against Jerusalem to battle, and
        the city shall be taken and the houses plundered and the women raped. Half
        of the city shall go out into exile, but the rest of the people shall not
        be cut off from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will go out and fight against
        those nations as when he fights on a day of battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On that day his feet shall stand on the Mount of Olives that lies
        before Jerusalem on the east, and the Mount of Olives shall be split in two
        from east to west by a very wide valley, so that one half of the Mount shall
        move northward, and the other half southward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And you shall flee to the valley of my mountains, for the valley
        of the mountains shall reach to Azal. And you shall flee as you fled from
        the earthquake in the days of Uzziah king of Judah. Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God will come, and all the holy ones with him.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:5 '
        content: 'Other Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  On that day there shall be no light, cold, or frost.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:6 '
        content: Compare Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate, Targum; the meaning of the
          Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And there shall be a unique[[COMMENT(0)]] day, which is known to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, neither day nor night, but at evening time
        there shall be light.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  On that day living waters shall flow out from Jerusalem, half of
        them to the eastern sea[[COMMENT(0)]] and half of them to the western sea. 
        It shall continue in summer as in winter.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:8 '
        content: That is, the Dead SeaThat is, the Mediterranean Sea
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be king over all the earth.
        On that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be one and his name one.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  The whole land shall be turned into a plain from Geba to Rimmon
        south of Jerusalem. But Jerusalem shall remain aloft on its site from the
        Gate of Benjamin to the place of the former gate, to the Corner Gate, and
        from the Tower of Hananel to the king\u2019s winepresses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it shall be inhabited, for there shall never again be a decree
        of utter destruction.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Jerusalem shall dwell in security.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:11 '
        content: The Hebrew term rendered refers to things devoted (or set apart)
          to the Lord (or by the Lord) for destruction
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And this shall be the plague with which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will strike all the peoples that wage war against Jerusalem: their flesh
        will rot while they are still standing on their feet, their eyes will rot
        in their sockets, and their tongues will rot in their mouths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And on that day a great panic from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        shall fall on them, so that each will seize the hand of another, and the
        hand of the one will be raised against the hand of the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Even Judah will fight at Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]] And the wealth
        of all the surrounding nations shall be collected, gold, silver, and garments
        in great abundance. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And a plague like this plague shall fall on the horses, the mules,
        the camels, the donkeys, and whatever beasts may be in those camps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then everyone who survives of all the nations that have come against
        Jerusalem shall go up year after year to worship the King, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, and to keep the Feast of Booths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And if any of the families of the earth do not go up to Jerusalem
        to worship the King, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, there will
        be no rain on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And if the family of Egypt does not go up and present themselves,
        then on them there shall be no rain;[[COMMENT(0)]] there shall be the plague
        with which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> afflicts the nations that do not
        go up to keep the Feast of Booths. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'This shall be the punishment to Egypt and the punishment to all the
        nations that do not go up to keep the Feast of Booths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And on that day there shall be inscribed on the bells of the horses,
        \u201CHoly to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D And the pots in the
        house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> shall be as the bowls before the
        altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And every pot in Jerusalem and Judah shall be holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, so that all who sacrifice may come and take of them and boil the
        meat of the sacrifice in them. And there shall no longer be a trader[[COMMENT(0)]]
        in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts on that day.
      comments:
      - number: '14:21 '
        content: 'Or '
